<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="set-v">set <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /set/    美 /set/  </p>
<p>(set, set)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-vt">1.★ <strong>vt 放；摆放；使处于 (某地)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>set the table</strong> for dinner
摆好桌子准备吃饭</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She set the piano against the wall.
她把钢琴靠墙摆放。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The house is set in (= located) fifty acres of parkland.
那所房子周围是50英亩的绿地。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-vt">2.★ <strong>vt 使...开始；使...处于 (某种状态)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>set a fire
点火</p></div>

<ul>
<li>set sb / sth + adv / prep / adj:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Her manner immediately set everyone comfortably.
她的态度立刻使大家感到轻松。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The firm’s accounts need to be set in order.
公司的账目需要清理。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Three years ago, five parrots were <strong>set free</strong> in a wild place.
3年前，5只鹦鹉在野外被放飞。</p></div>

<ul>
<li>set sb / sth doing sth:</li>
</ul>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Your report has set me thinking.
你的报告引起了我的思考。</p><footer>2010 北京</footer></div>

<h4 id="3-vt">3.★ <strong>vt 设置；调整：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>set</strong> her <strong>alarm</strong> for 7 o’clock.
她把闹钟设到了7点。</p></div>

<h4 id="4-vt">4.★ <strong>vt 确定 (价值、目标、日期等)；制定：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>set a price of $50,000 on the painting
给那幅画定价5万美元</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>set a goal</strong> / rule 
确定目标/制定规则</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>set a wedding dat<strong>set a date</strong>
确定婚期</p></div>

<h4 id="5-vt">5.★ <strong>vt 布置；安排：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The teacher set the students a lot of homework.
老师给学生留了很多家庭作业。</p></div>

<h4 id="6-vt">6.★ <strong>vt 树立 (榜样)；开创 (新风尚等)；创造 (纪录)：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She has <strong>set a good example for</strong> us.
她给我们树立了好榜样。</p><footer>2010 浙江</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rock stars often <strong>set fashions</strong> in clothes.
摇滚歌星常开创时装的新式样。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>set a new world record</strong> for the high jump.
她创造了一项新的世界跳高纪录。</p></div>

<h4 id="7-vt">7.★ <strong>vt [常用于被动语态] 以...为背景：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Great Expectations <strong>is set in</strong> England in the early 1800s.
《远大前程》以19世纪早期的英国为背景。</p><footer>译林⑧ – 1</footer></div>

<h4 id="8-vi">8.★ <strong>vi (日、月等) 落：</strong></h4>
<p>反 rise </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We watched the sun setting.
我们看着太阳落下。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="set-about">set about</h3>
<p>1.<strong>开始；着手：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I set about researching the habits of snakes so I could trap them in the easiest way. 
我着手研究蛇的习性，以便用最简单的方法捕捉它们。</p><footer>人教⑧ – 3</footer></div>

<h3 id="set-aside">set aside</h3>
<p>1.<strong>留出；把…置于一旁：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Set aside some time each day to write, even if it is only five minutes.
每天留出一点儿时间来写作，哪怕只有5分钟。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>set aside one’s work
放下工作</p></div>

<h3 id="set-down">set down</h3>
<p>1.<strong>记下；放下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I don’t want to set down a series of facts in a diary as most people do.
我不愿像大多数人那样在日记中记流水账。</p><footer>人教① – 1</footer></div>

<h3 id="set-in">set in</h3>
<p>1.<strong>开始；来临：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Panic set in, but Mary could not run — she was frozen to the spot.
玛丽开始感到恐惧，但是无法跑开——她吓呆了。</p><footer>2011 江西</footer></div>

<h3 id="set-off">set off</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>出发；动身：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We ought to set off at 7:00, while the roads are empty.
我们应该7点出发，趁那时路上没什么车。</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>触响（警报）；放（烟火）：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Some boys are setting off fireworks in the street.
一些男孩正在街上放烟火。</p></div>

<p>3.<strong>引发；激发：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>His rude reply set off a bad feeling of me.
他无礼的答复引起了我的反感。</p></div>

<h3 id="set-out">set out</h3>
<p>1.<strong>出发；打算；阐述：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When <strong>setting out on a</strong> long <strong>walk</strong>, always wear suitable shoes.
出发远行时，一定穿上合适的鞋子。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We <strong>set out to</strong> paint the whole house but finished only the front part that day.
那天我们打算把整个房子粉刷完，但只粉刷完了前面的部分。</p><footer>2012 全国</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He set out the reasons for his decision in his report.
他在报告中阐述了他作这个决定的理由。</p></div>

<h3 id="set-up">set up</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>建起；竖起；安装：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>set up camp
搭建营地</p></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>建立；设立；创立 (establish)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>set up a company</strong>
开公司</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>安排：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I set up an interview with her and we discussed her project at length.
我安排了一次与她面谈，详细地讨论了她的项目。</p><footer>2013湖南</footer></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>Ralph W. Emerson would always set <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ new ideas that occurred to him.  （2014 陕西改）  </li>
<li>Traditionally, college students hold a graduation ceremony to encourage themselves before they set <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ on their life journey.  （2013 安徽改）  </li>
<li>In much of the animal world, night is the time set <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ for sleep — pure and simple.  （2013 湖北改）  </li>
<li>Armed with the information you have gathered, you can set about <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ (prepare) your business plan.   （2012 浙江改）  </li>
<li>For all three years I have been working for others. I’m hoping I’ll set <strong><em>_</em></strong>_ my own business someday.  （2006 江西改）  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. down  2. off  3. aside  4. preparing  5. up  </p></div>